    <text>
       
        <front>
            <div type="editorial_desc">
                <p>The image depicts a lodging-house filled with sleeping immigrant laborers.  The beds are labeled "German, Englishman, Irishman, Chinaman, Italian, Russian, Negro, Spaniard, and Frenchman.  The Irishman disturbs everyone in lodge who is trying to sleep.  The Irishman throws bricks and shouts at Uncle Sam who covers his ears.  In the background, Columbia also covers her ears to protect herself from the noise.</p>
                <p>In the editorial which accompanies the cartoon, the editors claim that all immigrant groups except the Irish have successfully integrated themselves into American society.  According to the editors, immigrants "should not come here to trouble himself and others with the dissensions and grievances of his native land." This viewpoint is represented in the political cartoon by the bricks labeled with Irish causes such as "Irish Independence."  There are several stereotypical representations of ethnic groups in the cartoon.  For example, the Irishman holds a bottle of "Rye" while the Chinese man holds an opium pipe.   </p>
            </div>
        </front>

        <body>
            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Title" n="1">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Title and Caption</supplied></head>
                <p>UNCLE SAM'S LODGING-HOUSE</p>
                <p>Uncle Sam:-"Look here, you, everybody else is quiet and peaceable, and you're all the time a-kicking up a row!"</p>
                <p><add>June 7 1882</add></p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Caption_1" n="2">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Address of <orgName key="ENT.000000384">Puck</orgName></supplied></head>
                <p>OFFICE OF <hi rendition="#bold">"PUCK"</hi> 23 WARREN ST. NEW YORK.</p>
            </div>
            
            
            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Caption_2" n="3">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Address of <orgName key="ENT.000000380">Mayer, Merkel, &amp; Ottmann</orgName></supplied></head>
                <p>MAYER MERKEL &amp; OTTMANN. LITH. 23-25 WARREN ST. N.Y.</p>
                
            </div>
            
            
            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Artist" n="4">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial"><persName key="ENT.000000379">Joseph Ferdinand Keppler</persName></supplied></head>
                <p>J. KEPPLER</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Puck" n="5">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial"><orgName key="ENT.000000384">Puck</orgName></supplied></head>
                <p>PUCK.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Lowell" n="6">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Bricks 1-3</supplied></head>
                <p>RECALL <persName key="ENT.000003641">LOWELL</persName>.</p>
                <p>AGITATION</p>
                <p>AN IRISH MINISTER TO ENGLAND.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Chinese" n="7">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Brick 4</supplied></head>
                <p>THE CHINESE MUST GO.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Independence" n="8">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Brick 5</supplied></head>
                <p>IRISH INDEPENDENCE</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Ethnicity_1" n="9">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Bottom Row of Beds</supplied></head>
                <p>GERMAN.</p>
                <p>ENGLISHMAN.</p>
                <p>IRISHMAN.</p>
                <p>CHINA<supplied resp="editorial">MAN.</supplied></p>
                <p>ITALIAN.</p>
                
            </div>
            
            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Ethnicity_2" n="10">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Top Row of Beds</supplied></head>
                <p>RUSSIAN</p>
                <p>NEGRO</p>
                <p>SPANIARD.</p>
                <p>JAPANESE</p>
                <p>FRENCHMAN.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Table" n="11">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Table</supplied></head>
                <p>J. Baumann</p>
                <p><unclear reason="handwriting">Erlan</unclear></p>
                
            </div>
            
           <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Bottle" n="12">
               <head><supplied resp="editorial">Bottle</supplied></head>
               <p>RYE <note n="1" type="editorial">Some Americans believed that most Irish immigrants abused alcohol.  The political cartoon highlights this stereotype by depicting a bottle of rye whiskey in the Irishman's bed.</note></p>
           </div>
            
            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Boot" n="13">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Boot</supplied></head>
                <p>NO RENT</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Bag" n="14">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Bag</supplied></head>
                <p>LONDON</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="image_annotation" facs="#Sam" n="15">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial"><rs resp="cartoons_symbols.xml#uncle_sam">Uncle Sam</rs></supplied></head>
                <p>Image shows Uncle Sam in his pajamas, carries a lantern, and covers his ears.</p>
               
            </div>
            
            <div type="image_annotation" facs="#Columbia" n="16">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial"><rs resp="cartoons_symbols.xml#columbia">Columbia</rs></supplied></head>
                <p>Columbia covers her ears.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="image_annotation" facs="#Pipe" n="17">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial"><rs resp="cartoons_symbols.xml#columbia">Opium Pipe</rs></supplied></head>
                <p>Some native-born americans believed that Chinese immigrants abused opium. The political cartoon highlights this Chinese immigrant stereotype by depicting the Chinese man asleep next to his opium pipe.</p>
            </div>
            
            
            
            
            
